Fatigue Effects - Compare 1st and 2nd Quartiles (Top Performers)

full_df %>%
  mutate(did_mult = if_else(pid %in% did_mult$pid,T,F)) %>% 
  mutate(`Problem Type` = if_else(class=='Standard','Common','Exceptional')) %>%
    filter(!is.na(class)) %>% 
    filter(module=='MATH_FLUENCY') %>% 
  mutate(test_minute = case_when(trial_onset/1000 < 60 ~ 1,
                                 trial_onset/1000 > 120 ~ 3,
                                 T~2)) %>% 
  mutate(trial_onset = trial_onset/1000) %>% 
  group_by(pid,grade) %>% 
  mutate(rcs = (60*sum(answered_correctly, na.rm = T))/sum(firstButtonRT, na.rm = T)) %>% ungroup() %>% 
  select(pid,grade,test_minute,rcs,answered_correctly,firstButtonRT,question_text,did_mult) %>% 
  group_by(did_mult) %>% 
  mutate(perf_quartile = ntile(rcs, 4)) %>% 
  select(-rcs) %>% 
  mutate(perf_quartile = if_else(did_mult==T, 4, perf_quartile)) %>% 
  filter(perf_quartile==4) %>% 
  group_by(pid,did_mult,test_minute) %>%
  summarise(rcs = (60*sum(answered_correctly, na.rm = T))/sum(firstButtonRT, na.rm = T),n_items = n()) %>%
  ungroup() %>% 
  group_by(did_mult,test_minute) %>% 
  summarise(mean_rcs = mean(rcs, na.rm=T),
            se_rcs = sd(rcs, na.rm=T)/sqrt(n()),
            mean_nitems = mean(n_items, na.rm=T),
            count=n()) %>% 
  mutate(did_mult = if_else(did_mult==T, 'Highest','High'),
         test_minute = as.factor(test_minute)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = did_mult, y = mean_rcs, fill = test_minute)) +
  geom_col(position = position_dodge(width = 0.9)) +  # Group the bars
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_rcs - se_rcs, ymax = mean_rcs + se_rcs),
                position = position_dodge(width = 0.9), width = 0.25) +  # Add error bars
  labs(x = "Performance Group", y = "Correct Responses per Minute", fill = "Minute") +  # Labels
  theme_bw()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'pid', 'did_mult'. You can override using
## the `.groups` argument.
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'did_mult'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.

stats_df = full_df %>%
  mutate(did_mult = if_else(pid %in% did_mult$pid,T,F)) %>% 
  mutate(`Problem Type` = if_else(class=='Standard','Common','Exceptional')) %>%
    filter(!is.na(class)) %>% 
    filter(module=='MATH_FLUENCY') %>% 
  mutate(test_minute = case_when(trial_onset/1000 < 60 ~ 1,
                                 trial_onset/1000 > 120 ~ 3,
                                 T~2)) %>% 
  mutate(trial_onset = trial_onset/1000) %>% 
  group_by(pid,grade) %>% 
  mutate(rcs = (60*sum(answered_correctly, na.rm = T))/sum(firstButtonRT, na.rm = T)) %>% ungroup() %>% 
  select(pid,grade,test_minute,rcs,answered_correctly,firstButtonRT,question_text,did_mult) %>% 
  group_by(did_mult) %>% 
  mutate(perf_quartile = ntile(rcs, 4)) %>% 
  select(-rcs) %>% 
  mutate(perf_quartile = if_else(did_mult==T, 4, perf_quartile)) %>% 
  filter(perf_quartile==4) %>% 
  group_by(pid,did_mult,test_minute) %>%
  summarise(rcs = (60*sum(answered_correctly, na.rm = T))/sum(firstButtonRT, na.rm = T),n_items = n())
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'pid', 'did_mult'. You can override using
## the `.groups` argument.
mod = lm(rcs~did_mult*test_minute, data = stats_df)
summary(mod)
